-- U.S. RESEARCH ROUNDUP-Huntington Bancshares, Charter Communications 
-- 
-- Mon Jul 21, 2014 02:31AM EDT
-- None



July 21 (Reuters) - Wall Street securities analysts revised their ratings and price targets on several U.S.-listed companies, including Huntington Bancshares, Imax Corp and Coca-Cola Co, on Monday.

HIGHLIGHTS * Huntington Bancshares <HBAN.O>: Sandler O'neill raises to buy from hold * IMAX Corp <IMAX.N>: Stifel raises to buy from hold  * Charter Communications <CHTR.O>: ISI Group raises target price to $180 from $145; buy   Following is a summary of research actions on U.S. companies reported by Reuters on Monday. Stock entries are in alphabetical order.* Bank Of New York Mellon <BK.N>: RBC raises target price to $40 from $34; sector perform  * Charter Communications <CHTR.O>: ISI Group raises target price to $180 from $145; buy  * Dish Network <DISH.O>: ISI Group raises target price to $73 from $61; rating buy  * Huntington Bancshares <HBAN.O>: Sandler O'neill raises to buy from hold * Imax Corp <IMAX.N>: Stifel raises to buy from hold  * Lions Gate Entertainment <LGF.N>: B. Riley raises target price to $40; rating buy * Nimble Storage <NMBL.N>: Pacific Crest raises price target to $44 from $42; outperform